The paper discusses the creation of a dataset using data mining and RDF technology, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The use of machine learning and artificial intelligence methods for drug-drug interaction prediction suggests the paper could also fit under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of text mining and information retrieval techniques, which could place it under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of statistical validation methods and the mention of decision making variables suggests the paper could also fit under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the curation of mappings between drug names and identifiers, which could place it under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
